criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male or female participants aged ≥65 years;

          -  Community-dwelling older adults;

          -  Older adults who have fallen in the last 6 months or who are at high risk of falling
             (scoring ≤25 points on Fullerton Advanced Balance Scale);

          -  Participation agreement;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of severe cognitive decline (patients with a Mini-Mental State Examination
             ≤9);

          -  Fracture in one or both lower limbs for less than 4 months;

          -  Diagnosed of health conditions compromising the program participation, such as: severe
             osteoporosis (T ≤ 2.5, with the occurrence of one or more associated osteoporotic
             fractures); hip or knee prostheses; incapacitating cardiovascular conditions;
             epilepsy; cancer or metastases;

          -  Do not wish to participate in the study;
